fields.name: Aeronautical Engineering
fields.description: Deals with the design, construction, and study of the science behind the forces and physical properties of aircraft, rockets, and spacecraft.

fields.name: Agricultural Engineering
fields.description: Applies engineering science and technology to agricultural production and processing.

fields.name: Artificial Intelligence and Robotics Engineering
fields.description: Focuses on creating intelligent machines and robots that can work and react like humans.

fields.name: Biomedical Engineering
fields.description: A multidisciplinary field that combines biology and engineering, applying engineering principles to medicine and healthcare.

fields.name: Chemical Engineering
fields.description: Involves the production and manufacturing of products through chemical processes.

fields.name: Civil Engineering
fields.description: Deals with the design, construction, and maintenance of the physical and naturally built environment, including works like roads, bridges, and canals.

fields.name: Computer Science Engineering
fields.description: Integrates several fields of computer science required to develop computer hardware and software.

fields.name: Electrical Engineering
fields.description: Deals with the study, design, and application of equipment, devices, and systems which use electricity, electronics, and electromagnetism.

fields.name: Electronics and Communication Engineering
fields.description: Involves designing, developing, and testing electronic equipment used in various systems.

fields.name: Mechanical Engineering
fields.description: Applies engineering, physics, and materials science principles to design, analyze, manufacture, and maintain mechanical systems.

fields.name: Metallurgical Engineering
fields.description: The study of the physical and chemical behavior of metallic elements, their inter-metallic compounds, and their mixtures, which are called alloys.

fields.name: Mining Engineering
fields.description: Associated with the practice, theory, science, technology, and application of extracting and processing minerals from a naturally occurring environment.

fields.name: Petroleum Engineering
fields.description: Concerned with the activities related to the production of hydrocarbons, which can be either crude oil or natural gas.

fields.name: Production Engineering
fields.description: A combination of manufacturing technology with management science.

fields.name: Robotics Engineering
fields.description: An interdisciplinary branch of engineering and science that includes mechanical engineering, electrical engineering, computer science, and others.

fields.name: Structural Engineering
fields.description: A specialty within civil engineering in which structural engineers are trained to design the 'bones and muscles' that create the form and shape of man-made structures.

fields.name: Telecommunication Engineering
fields.description: Focuses on electrical and computer engineering which seeks to support and enhance telecommunication systems.
